{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:42.638219+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_88d6c449-fd07-4fea-b24e-31123b99c46b"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n    cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n\n    container = profile[\"container\"]\n    if container == \"gif\":\n        # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n        fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n        cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n    else:\n        video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n        audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n        cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n        if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n        if \"crf\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n        if scale and scale != \"source\":\n            cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n\n    cmd.append(str(output_path))\n    return cmd\n\n\ndef run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n    return subprocess.call(cmd)\n", "id": "lc_66f9426e-08e0-4141-b8d6-76f5793095df"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f7a586d4-d5fd-4574-bda3-8e3dcd080577", "tool_call_id": "call_88996dd577a949f3a16e321c", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:58.680448+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have a clear picture. Let me summarize my findings:\n\n**Issue #1** reports that `vidpack gif` produces washed-out/banded GIF output compared to tools like gifski or a manual two-pass ffmpeg palette pipeline.\n\n**Evidence from the codebase:**\n\n1. **`profiles.toml`** (line 15-18) already acknowledges this as a known limitation:\n   > \"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"\n\n2. **`runner.py`** (lines 14-17) confirms the single-pass approach — it only applies `fps` and `scale` filters for GIF, with no palette generation (`palettegen`/`paletteuse` filters).\n\n3. **`README.md`** table says `(palette)` for the gif video codec, which is slightly misleading since no palette generation actually happens.\n\nThe issue is a valid, confirmed known limitation — it's already documented in the source. I'll add a comment acknowledging this and linking it to the existing documentation so the reporter knows it's a recognized area for improvement.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 746, "prompt_tokens": 8472, "total_tokens": 9218, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 203, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8000, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.00088314, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.00023412, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00064902}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864182-phkJvPqMNUciJSSh2SS3", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c6-e96e-7752-ac62-e0608eaded1d-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the detailed report, @BruceKZ! I've triaged this against the current codebase and confirmed the behavior you described is indeed the current design.\n\n**Findings:**\n\n1. **`runner.py`** — the GIF code path only applies `fps` and `scale` filters (single-pass). There is no `palettegen` / `paletteuse` filter chain, so ffmpeg falls back to its default (global) palette, which causes the banding you observed.\n\n2. **`profiles.toml`** — the project already acknowledges this as a known limitation in a comment on the `gif` section:\n   > *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"*\n\nSo this issue is valid and accurately captured. A two-pass approach (generate palette → apply palette) would meaningfully improve GIF color quality. The implementation would involve splitting the ffmpeg invocation into two steps or using a filter_complex chain.\n\nLeaving this open as a confirmed enhancement. 🏷️ Labeling accordingly."}, "id": "call_7f76fcf87bb44de4be5034f4", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8472, "output_tokens": 746, "total_tokens": 9218, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8000}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 203}}}}]}}}
