{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:30:11.090137+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, the personal access token doesn't have write permissions for this repository, so I can't post comments or update labels. Here's my triage summary:\n\n---\n\n## Triage Summary: Issue #1 — \"gif profile output looks washed out / banded\"\n\n**Status:** ✅ Valid / Confirmed — known limitation already documented in codebase.\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n| Source | What it shows |\n|---|---|\n| `runner.py` (L14-17) | GIF path uses only `fps` + `scale` filters — no `palettegen`/`paletteuse`, so ffmpeg uses a default global palette → banding |\n| `profiles.toml` (L15-18) | A developer comment already calls this out as a \"known limitation\" and says it's \"tracked in the issue tracker\" |\n| `README.md` table | Says GIF uses `(palette)` — slightly misleading since no palette generation actually occurs |\n\n**Recommended action:** Leave the issue open and label it `enhancement`. The fix would be to implement a proper two-pass palette pipeline (either two separate ffmpeg calls, or a single call using `-filter_complex` with `split[pal][vid];[pal]palettegen[p];[vid][p]paletteuse`). The `profiles.toml` comment already anticipates this.\n\n**Blocker:** I was unable to post a comment or update labels due to a `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token` error — the token lacks write access to this repository.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 339, "prompt_tokens": 9226, "total_tokens": 9565, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 20, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9024, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0004152864, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001